race.comment: REEL HOT (2) delivered his Maiden at Warrnambool enjoying the firmer surface and step up to 1700m. Fourth up now and the middle distance shouldn't pose an issue. Keep the in-form Yendall and he looks capable of going back-to-back. MY UNCLE DID IT (9) disappointed as favourite over 1700m at Warrnambool behind Brung King but her nose defeat at Terang prior was good. She should enjoy a soft run and over the longer trip is worth another chance. COASTAL WHISPERS (12) went close at Mornington over 200m and then tackled a staying trip there in stronger than this and found it a bit tough. This suits a lot better and she's also a chance. Ditto MON ETOILE (14), who peaks and is busting to win. She will run it right out under Gordon.
